(1 inline comment)

Hello Noboru Arai, thanks for you commit. I have one inline comments.

Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

I think try/except works and makes sense. Why we need to check the length of args?

Patch Set 1:

Hi Fei,

I can see your comment, I though the same thing.
After reading the commit log and the code, I maybe see the purpose.

The commands should be specified with *one* argument(image-id).
However if specifying multiple arguments, an argument error does not happen and the last argument is used.

This patch fixes the behavior.

Arai-san, please let me know if I misunderstand it.

Patch Set 1: (1 inline comment)

Ken'ichi, thanks for the clarification. It makes more sense. If that's the root cause, then I prefer to use: image_id = args.pop(0)

Patch Set 1:

Thanks oomichi-sann, that is right.

I executed "glance-cach-manage" command as follows.
  ?"glance-cache manage queue-image <image-id1> <image-id2>"
 
"queue-iamge" sub command must be one "image-id",but
argumentbut "glance-cach-manage" command continues and <image-id2> is queued.

Because I think number of <image-id> is shoud be one,
"len(args) == 1" check is added.

Patch Set 1:

Thanks Fei, I reply your comment.
 * I prefer to use: image_id = args.pop(0)

In the case of above modifcation, first argument is selected
in multiple argument.
 ex)
  glance-cache-image queue-image <image-id1> <image-id2> <image-id3>
  -> <image-id1> is selected and queued.
     <image-id2>/<image-id3> is ignored.

Because this command is user command(*),  I think check of number is critical.

* http://docs.openstack.org/developer/glance/cache.html
